commitResults.messageBody:
Implement a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user,
simply echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types bye.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add the ability to add and display added items.
commitResults.messageBody:
Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user
and display them back to the user when requested.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add the ability to mark tasks as done.
Add support for tracking three types of tasks.
commitResults.messageBody:
1. ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it
2. Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time
3. Events: tasks that start at a specific time and ends at a specific time

Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate
the testing of Duke and add more comments in code.

commitResults.messageTitle: Handle errors of incorrect user inputs.
Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
Use Java enums for command keywords.
